author: Peter Goff
title: Wuhan’s Irish emerge blinking in sunlight as coronavirus controls ease
description: As Hubei province creaked open its gates this week after more than two months of stringent shutdown, the first walk many residents took was to the local funeral home to collect the ashes of their loved ones. Winding, well-spaced queues formed outside the city…
